<br>
I would say that I agree with some, not all, of the subject matter of the post.<br>
<br>
It is apparent that some abilities are not being factored in balance of the class.<br>
<br>
While I agree whole-heartedly that wizards should be tweaked (not totally revamped) to be more group friendly, other capabilities should not be ignored.<br>
<br>
Soloing is VERY boring.  Very.  But - it is something that can be done.  A warrior past around level 20 (arguably less) cannot solo effectively.<br>
<br>
To make the changes that are being presented, you would have to do one of two things:  Allow warriors (or all melee that is being compared to for that matter) capable of soloing a third as well as wizards OR make wizards solo ability far, far less than it currently is.<br>
<br>
Neither of these will ever fly.  One of the two parties would cry foul, and I can pretty much guarantee which one.  Wizards would go ballistic if solo capability was taken, and would complain heavily if warriors and other melee were given effective solo ability.  Not so much the second, as it doesn't affect the wizard too much.<br>
<br>
I agree that soloing is boring, and generally only used as an alternative to grouping.  However, I (44 wiz currently) leveled quickly in The Overthere by soloing.  Made it through level 40 in 2 days.  It took my warrior (49 currently) about 3 weeks to perform the same feat.<br>
<br>
Wizards also have the ability that only one other class does.  Gates.  Not ports, gates.  Ports are convenient, but that’s about it.  Gates, however, can come in handy when it comes to grouping.<br>
<br>
When I’m LFG, I don’t sit at Karnor’s hoping to be picked like the unathletic, antisocial mole of a kid being picked for lunchtime handball.  I go to numerous places.  I gate all around and usually get a group fairly quickly.  Even though I might have gotten more experience or better loot at Ruins 3, I could be having just as much fun in Lower Guk, Sol B, Eastern Wastes, Great Divide, etc.<br>
<br>
Warriors have to pretty much be where they want to group.  Not much option other than hoofing it.<br>
<br>
Again, I agree that wizards should be tweaked to be more desired in groups.  But I’ll be damned if I think that wizards aren’t powerful.  Even if I don’t have ports.  I have snare, awesome AEs, amazing nukes, etc.  I’m happy to be a wizard.  <br>
<br>
And for clarification…<br>
<br>
A tank missing is a full resist<br>
A tank hitting for less is a partial resist<br>
A tank getting riposted is a fizzle.  <br>
<br>
A wizard fizzling wastes mana (read: hitting ability).  A warrior getting riposted lowers tanking ability (read: absorbing damage).  Not directly lowering ability, but a dead warrior does as much good as a wizard OOM.<br>
<br>
I love my warrior.  I love my wizard.  I think that by playing both characters up to a relatively high level I can appreciate the benefits and flaws to both characters.  When I want to knock the living crap out of something while laughing maniacally and having it beat on me I play my warrior.  When I want to nuke the hell out of something and show it who it’s daddy is, I play my wizard.  I feel fortunate to have the option.<br>
<br>
Again, sorry for the rant/rave/flame/smacking/novel, but sometimes I just need to get my word in.<br>
<br>
I’m probably going to get this ripped apart by the others here, and I openly accept that.  There’s a lot of very smart wizards and other classes that post to this forum, and I feel that any input is good as long as it’s constructive.<br>
<br>
Thank you, drive through.<br>
<br>
Manalow Gottamed<br>
44th Level Wizard<br>
Bristlebane Server<br>
<br>
Chaotic Conformity<br>
49th Level Warrior<br>
